@startuml SCRUM-62 Auction Q&A

title Buyer Ask Question & Seller Reply (SCRUM-62)

actor Buyer as B
actor Seller as S
participant "Browser\n(auction-detail.jsp)" as UI
participant "AuctionDetailServlet\nGET /auction/{id}" as ADS
participant "AuctionQuestionServlet\nGET /auction-question" as AQS_GET
participant "AuctionQuestionServlet\nPOST /protected/auction-question" as AQS_POST
participant "QuestionDAO" as DAO
participant "AuthFilter\n(/protected/*)" as AF
database "PostgreSQL\n(auction_questions)" as DB

== View listing with Q&A (public) ==

B -> UI : Open /auction/42
UI -> ADS : GET /auction/42
activate ADS
ADS -> DAO : listByAuction(42)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT q.*, u.username\n  FROM auction_questions q JOIN users u\n  WHERE auction_id = ? ORDER BY created_at ASC
DB --> DAO : rows
DAO --> ADS : List<AuctionQuestion>
deactivate DAO
ADS -> ADS : set canAsk (buyer, not seller, open)\n     canAnswer (seller, isSelf)
ADS -> UI : forward auction-detail.jsp\n  (questions + timestamps via <c:out>)
deactivate ADS
UI -> B : Display Q&A thread with askedAt / answeredAt

== Alternative GET list endpoint ==

B -> AQS_GET : GET /auction-question?auctionId=42
activate AQS_GET
AQS_GET -> AQS_GET : parse auctionId (long)\n  invalid → 400
AQS_GET -> DAO : listByAuction(42)
DAO -> DB : same SELECT
DB --> DAO : rows
AQS_GET -> UI : redirect /auction/42#questions
deactivate AQS_GET

== Buyer asks a question ==

B -> UI : Submit question form (action=ASK)
UI -> AF : POST /protected/auction-question\n  action=ASK&auctionId=42&question=...
activate AF
AF -> AF : session required → else redirect /login
AF -> AQS_POST : forward POST
activate AQS_POST

note right of AQS_POST
  <b>SCRUM-353 security:</b>
  • RbacUtil.isBuyer(session) → else 403
  • askerId from session only (no IDOR)
  • auctionId parsed as long → 400 if invalid
  • seller cannot ask on own auction (DAO check)
  • blank question → 400
  • InputValidator length check
  • SecurityUtil.sanitize(question) before persist
end note

AQS_POST -> AQS_POST : isBuyer? askerId from session
AQS_POST -> AQS_POST : validate question not blank\n  InputValidator.getQuestionViolation()\n  SecurityUtil.sanitize()
AQS_POST -> DAO : insertQuestion(42, askerId, sanitizedText)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : BEGIN\n  SELECT seller_id, date_end, moderation_state FROM auction WHERE auction_id=?\n  reject if not found / self / closed\n  INSERT INTO auction_questions ...
DB --> DAO : OK
DAO --> AQS_POST : QuestionResult.SUCCESS
deactivate DAO
AQS_POST -> AQS_POST : session.questionFlash = success
AQS_POST -> UI : redirect /auction/42#questions
deactivate AQS_POST
deactivate AF
UI -> B : Flash + updated Q&A list

== Seller replies ==

S -> UI : Submit reply form (action=REPLY)
UI -> AF : POST /protected/auction-question\n  action=REPLY&questionId=7&answer=...
AF -> AQS_POST : forward POST
activate AQS_POST

note right of AQS_POST
  <b>SCRUM-353 reply security:</b>
  • RbacUtil.isSeller(session) → else 403
  • sellerId from session only
  • questionId parsed as long → 400
  • DAO verifies question.auction.seller_id = sellerId\n    wrong seller → 403 (NOT_SELLER)
  • sanitize answer text (XSS)
end note

AQS_POST -> AQS_POST : isSeller? sellerId from session
AQS_POST -> DAO : insertReply(7, sellerId, sanitizedAnswer)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT q.auction_id, a.seller_id, q.answer_text\n  FROM auction_questions q JOIN auction a\n  WHERE q.id = ?
DAO -> DB : UPDATE auction_questions\n  SET answer_text=?, answered_at=NOW()\n  WHERE id=? AND answer_text IS NULL
DB --> DAO : 1 row updated
DAO --> AQS_POST : QuestionResult.SUCCESS
deactivate DAO
AQS_POST -> UI : redirect /auction/{auctionId}#questions
deactivate AQS_POST
UI -> S : Reply visible with answeredAt timestamp

== Wrong seller reply → 403 ==

S -> AQS_POST : POST action=REPLY (seller B tries to reply on seller A's auction)
AQS_POST -> DAO : insertReply(...)
DAO --> AQS_POST : QuestionResult.NOT_SELLER
AQS_POST -> S : HTTP 403 Forbidden

@enduml
